---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import houseImage from "../assets/images/house.jpg";

const experienceInYears = new Date().getFullYear() - 2020;
const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<BaseLayout title="nbr.haus">
  <section>
    <img class="house-image" src={houseImage.src} alt="House" />

    <h2>About</h2>
    <p>
      Software Engineer with {experienceInYears} years of experience building frontend architectures and design systems. Currently
      seeking new opportunities starting February 2026.
    </p>

    <p>Born in 1984, based in Landshut, Germany. Outside of code, I enjoy hiking, running, and photography.</p>

    <h2>Work</h2>
    <h3>DealerCenter Digital — Software Engineer (2020-{currentYear})</h3>
    <p>
      Led major architectural migrations across a mature Electron application serving bike retailers. Designed and
      implemented a <strong>comprehensive 10-variant color system</strong> with
      <strong>Figma integration</strong>, affecting the entire codebase. Migrated the application from <strong
        >legacy Redux to Redux Toolkit</strong
      > and championed <strong>TanStack Query adoption</strong> with comprehensive <strong
        >code guidelines and best practices documentation</strong
      >. Built BikeCenter's <strong>custom design system from scratch</strong> using React, TypeScript, and SCSS. Completely rebuilt
      a Vendure storefront from a <strong>Remix template to TanStack Start/Router</strong> with TanStack Form, GraphQL, and Tailwind
      CSS.
    </p>
    <p>
      Established <strong>technical standards</strong> and <strong>coding conventions</strong> across the team, including <strong
        >translation guidelines</strong
      >, <strong>BEM naming conventions</strong>, and <strong>TypeScript best practices</strong>. <strong
        >Mentored junior developers</strong
      >
      through pair programming and code reviews, creating extensive documentation for knowledge transfer. Coordinated cross-functional
      teams as <strong>technical hub</strong> between management, backend, and frontend, facilitating communication and ensuring
      alignment on architectural decisions.
    </p>

    <h3>diva-e — Junior Frontend Developer (2020)</h3>
    <p>
      Worked on BayWa's e-commerce platform at a digital agency. Built features with their design system, <strong
        >created documentation for an undocumented internal framework</strong
      >, and developed an internal Instagram-like tool using React, GraphQL, and Apollo. Started during COVID-19, worked
      primarily remote while onboarding independently.
    </p>

    <h3>Campudus — Intern (2019-2020)</h3>
    <p>
      Built a fullstack accessories ordering application from scratch (design, architecture, backend, frontend) during a
      3-month internship at DealerCenter Digital's sister company.
    </p>

    <h2>Projects</h2>
    <h3>Black Atom — <a href="https://black-atom.industries">black-atom.industries</a></h3>
    <p>
      Open-source theming system with 27+ themes across 6 platforms (Neovim, Zed, Ghostty, WezTerm, Tmux, and more). Built
      with an <strong>adapter pattern</strong> for consistent theme generation from a central source using <strong
        >OKLCH color space</strong
      >. Maintained with focus on developer experience and cross-platform consistency.
    </p>

    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
    <p>These are the technologies I'm familiar with and regularly use.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://react.dev">React</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.typescriptlang.org">TypeScript</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://graphql.org">GraphQL</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://tailwindcss.com">Tailwind CSS</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://tanstack.com/router">TanStack Router</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://tanstack.com/query">TanStack Query</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://tanstack.com/form">TanStack Form</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://ui.shadcn.com">ShadCN</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://sass-lang.com">SCSS</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://nodejs.org">Node.js</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.electronjs.org">Electron</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://redux-toolkit.js.org">Redux (Toolkit)</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Personal Development Environment</h2>
    <p>
      I am very passionate about workflow. You can check my <a href="https://github.com/nikbrunner/dots">dotfiles here</a>.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/nikbrunner/dots/tree/main/common/.config/nvim">Neovim</a> (Primary editor)
      </li>
      <li><a href="https://zed.dev">Zed</a> (Secondary editor)</li>
      <li><a href="https://ghostty.dev">Ghostty</a> (Terminal)</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/tmux/tmux/wiki">Tmux</a> (Terminal multiplexer)</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit">LazyGit</a> (Git GUI)</li>
      <li><a href="https://1password.com">1Password</a> (Password & Secrets manager)</li>
      <li><a href="https://claude.com/product/claude-code">Claude Code</a> (AI assistant)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>AI</h2>
    <p>
      My primary AI assistance tool is <strong><a href="https://claude.com/product/claude-code">Claude Code</a></strong>. I
      prioritize Claude's consistency and quality over chasing every new model release. The terminal integration aligns
      naturally with my workflow, where I spend most of my time.
    </p>

    <h2>Connect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://www.github.com/nikbrunner">GitHub</a></li>
      <li><a href="mailto:nbr.haus.persuader046@passmail.com">Email (Alias)</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nbru/">LinkedIn</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .house-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 40vh;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-hard);
    border: var(--border-size-1) solid var(--fg-accent);
    margin: var(--size-4) auto var(--size-8);
  }
</style>
